description:
Job Responsibilities:

Responsible for jewellery and product designs range from concept development, designs from conception to delivery, follow-up on product development, etc;
Conduct market research and analysis from time to time;
Participate ad-hoc assignments as assigned. 

Job Requirements:

Diploma or above in Jewellery Design;
Minimum 3 years solid experience in luxury fine jewellery and 24K gold product industries;
Strong sense of market trend and knowledge in jewellery/ornament production;
Extensive knowledge of diamonds and colored gems;
Passion for innovative design;
Creative, meticulous and a good team player;
Excellent presentation and communication skills; 
Proficiency in illustrator, Photoshop applications and 3D software;
Able to meet tight deadline;
Fluent in spoken & written English, Chinese and Mandarin;
Candidates with less experience will be considered as Junior Jewellery Designer.

Job description

Maintain the costing and pricing database;
Handle data input, filing and update the ERP system in timely and accurate manner;
Provide the back-end services to the Purchasing Department;
Other ad-hoc tasks as required.

Requirements

Diploma or above with minimum 2 years solid working experience in trading and manufacturing industry;
With experience in operating ERP system is a bonus; 
With Accounting LCCI level 2;
Proficiency in written English, Chinese;
Immediate available is preferred.
Welcome to explore more on our website at www.cnkjewellery.com

